explanation: The solution uses dynamic programming to build up a 2D table where dp[i][j] represents the minimum number of turns needed to print the substring from index i to j. It iterates over the string from right to left and for each substring, it checks all possible splits and updates the dp table accordingly. The final result is stored in dp[0][n - 1].

